For example, in the area of controlling objects in public spaces, we worked on a project where we experimented with short and succinct gestures rather than expansive ones.
The gestures were not recorded by the object camera, but by a bracelet that registered the movements of the bones and muscles.
It is still relatively large, but could theoretically be reduced to the size of a wristwatch.
But all in all, the future belongs to mixed control types, such as gestures and language.
- As the?
- We would ask me, for example, to pass you this soda can?
You say it and point to it at the same time.
- I usually just say it.
- Oh, that would be very difficult to see.
