- Not necessarily, but this is about mutual rapprochement.
I think that in the near future we will have to work primarily on the development of new types of sensors that make it possible to record people&#39;s reactions more precisely.
This can be laser sensors, for example, as they offer good resolution at depth, which is very important.
- Based on your work with the Xbox Kinect sensors, what are your demands on modern cameras?
Is it lacking resolution, depth or something else?
- The current generation is basically a good starting point for our work in the field of three-dimensional recognition.
Of course, 8 megapixels with a speed of 1000 fps would not be bad.
