I think the eighth breakthrough could well be the integration of tactile perception.
An interesting method at the moment is the use of the second hand as a somewhat unusual projection base.
She takes pressure very well!
But there are also technologies that are actually aimed at giving something tangible to the &quot;images in the air&quot;, for example the interference of some directional ultrasound beams in a certain point where the finger is located creates a feeling, but that for the moment is still so weak, as if someone blew on the palms of your hands.
