&quot;The laws will lead to serious, unintended consequences,&quot; says Scott McIntyre of British American Tobacco Australia.
Chinese and Indonesian counterfeiters will be offering far larger quantities of these products on the streets of Australia.
Others, however, say the laws have boosted their business.
Sandra Ha of Zico Import Pty Ltd, a small family business, notes that since the groups British American Tobacco, Britain&#39;s Imperial Tobacco, Philip Morris and Japan Tobacco joined forces two months ago, demand for cigarette cases and silicon lids to cover the unbearable packaging has surged failed at the Australian Supreme Court in their challenge to the laws.
